Can we break a specfic loop in multiple loop scripts

In Bash, the break command accepts an optional numeric argument representing the number of nested levels to exit. 

break: Exits the current (innermost) loop.
break 2: Exits the current loop and the one immediately above it.
break 3: Exits three levels of nesting.

cat break.sh
#!/bin/bash

# Outer Loop
for i in {1..3}; do
    echo "Outer loop: $i"

    # Inner Loop
    for j in {1..5}; do
        if [[ $j -eq 3 ]]; then
            echo "  Breaking out of BOTH loops at inner=$j"
            continue   # <--- Breaks out of the inner AND outer loop
        fi
        echo "  Inner loop: $j"
    done
        if [[ $i -eq 2 ]]; then
                echo "breaking out of both loops at outer=$i"
                break 2
fi
done

echo "Finished!"
